Class ApexUnitTestShouldNotUseSeeAllDataTrue

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sourceforge.pmd.AbstractPropertySource

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ApexParserVisitor, ImmutableLanguage, PropertySource, CodeClimateRule, Rule

    public class ApexUnitTestShouldNotUseSeeAllDataTrue
extends AbstractApexUnitTestRule

    It's a very bad practice to use @isTest(seeAllData=true) in Apex unit tests, because it opens up the existing database data for unexpected modification by tests.

    Author:
    a.subramanian
